As Abb LTD  (ABB) Stock Rose, Folketrygdfondet Boosted by $24.36 Million Its Stake

July 13, 2017 - By Marie Mckinney








Folketrygdfondet increased its stake in Abb Ltd. (ABB) by 956.37% based on its latest 2016Q4 regulatory filing with the SEC. Folketrygdfondet bought 1.16 million shares as the company’s stock rose 9.90% with the market. The institutional investor held 1.28M shares of the electrical products company at the end of 2016Q4, valued at $27.00 million, up from 121,292 at the end of the previous reported quarter. Folketrygdfondet who had been investing in Abb Ltd. for a number of months, seems to be bullish on the $55.41B market cap company. The stock declined 0.28% or $0.07 reaching $25.19 on the news. About 279,179 shares traded. ABB Ltd (ADR) (NYSE:ABB) has risen 23.97% since July 13, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 7.27% the S&P500.
More notable recent ABB Ltd (ADR) (NYSE:ABB) news were published by: Fool.com which released: “Is ABB Ltd (ADR) Destined for Greatness?” on June 10, 2014, also Finance.Yahoo.com with their article: “ABB Ltd. (ABB) Q2 Earnings Improve, Revenues Down Y/Y” published on July 21, 2016, Marketwatch.com published: “25.2367” on July 23, 2009. More interesting news about ABB Ltd (ADR) (NYSE:ABB) were released by: Fool.com and their article: “Forget ABB Ltd. (ADR) and Check Out This German Robot Maker” published on May 21, 2014 as well as Seekingalpha.com‘s news article titled: “ABB: The Worst Is Behind But The Future Is Overvalued” with publication date: May 10, 2017.
ABB Ltd (ADR) (NYSE:ABB) Ratings Coverage
Among 14 analysts covering ABB Ltd (NYSE:ABB), 7 have Buy rating, 2 Sell and 5 Hold. Therefore 50% are positive. ABB Ltd has $25 highest and $1800 lowest target. $22.33’s average target is -11.35% below currents $25.19 stock price. ABB Ltd had 28 analyst reports since August 21, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. The company was upgraded on Friday, December 11 by RBC Capital Markets. The stock has “Outperform” rating by RBC Capital Markets on Wednesday, January 25. RBC Capital Markets downgraded the shares of ABB in report on Wednesday, April 6 to “Sector Perform” rating. Morgan Stanley upgraded ABB Ltd (ADR) (NYSE:ABB) on Monday, December 12 to “Overweight” rating. The firm has “Neutral” rating given on Wednesday, October 5 by Robert W. Baird. The firm has “Neutral” rating by JP Morgan given on Wednesday, April 20. The firm has “Outperform” rating given on Monday, December 12 by Robert W. Baird. The rating was maintained by Morgan Stanley with “Buy” on Wednesday, April 19. The stock has “Underperform” rating by BNP Paribas on Tuesday, February 9. The firm has “Hold” rating by Jefferies given on Friday, October 9.


