Folketrygdfondet Rejects John Fredriksen’s Bid For Property Shares



Folketrygdfondet Rejects John Fredriksen’s Bid For Property SharesWednesday, 7 Jan 2015 










Folketrygdfondet, the Norwegian state pension fund, has rejected a bid from billionaire investor John Fredriksen for its stake in real estate company Norwegian Property, according to Reuters.
 
 
The fund holds an 8.49 percent stake in Norwegian Property. Geveran Trading, Fredriksen’s investment firm, has bid CZK10 (US$0.43) per share, but the pension fund says it considered the assets of the company to be worth more.
 
 
Read the original story here.

